      • getBuilderPluginRegistry

        @Namespace(value="nvinfer1")
 @NoException(value=true)
public static IPluginRegistry getBuilderPluginRegistry(nvinfer.EngineCapability capability)
        \brief Return the plugin registry for building a Standard engine, or nullptr if no registry exists. Also return nullptr if the input argument is not EngineCapability::kSTANDARD. Engine capabilities EngineCapability::kSTANDARD and EngineCapability::kSAFETY have distinct plugin registries. When building a Safety engine, use nvinfer1::getBuilderSafePluginRegistry(). Use IPluginRegistry::registerCreator from the registry to register plugins. Plugins registered in a registry associated with a specific engine capability are only available when building engines with that engine capability. There is no plugin registry for EngineCapability::kDLA_STANDALONE.
